text: I booked into Origin for the last 4 nights of my stay in Bali and could not have had a better time. The whole place is beautiful - stunning design, well thought out touches, excellent service, extremely comfortable rooms and communal areas and delicious breakfasts. The bed was super comfortable, outdoor bathroom was gorgeous and all the extras - towels, sarongs, body lotion, mosquito coils - greatly appreciated.  The location is not too far from the nearest restaurants and shops, but in reality the heat and hills means that a scooter is your best bet for getting around. I did use a bike from the property one day, but this was exhausting for more than a short journey. However they can easily arrange a scooter or taxi for you on request. They couldn't do enough to help me and I found the whole stay totally relaxing and peaceful. The one downside is that it's pretty noisy in the morning with the hens, and the geckos do screech at odd times during the night, so a decent pair of ear plugs comes recommended. I would stay here again in an instant, thank you!
title: Blissed out vibes with 5* service in Uluwatu

text:
We have just returned from an absolutely fantastic and memorable 4 night vacation at Origin Uluwatu. I cant praise this unique ‘boutique’ luxury tented experience enough. 

We have three kids aged 6,8,11 and they all loved it. We stayed in a 2 bedroom tent with a private pool. The private gardens/pool are a delight and the tents are fabulous, decorated to an amazingly high standard with excellent comfortable beds, beautiful bathroom and luxurious outdoor bath. I especially liked the cushion fabrics in the room and around the communal areas. Clearly a lot of thought went into the interior design of Origin. The kids enjoyed the fact that you could fully open up the tented front each day and step into the pool directly from the room. 

Origin also had a superb Geo-Dome which was especially fun for the kids and again, very unique. The Spa was also awesome and housed in its own tent. The massage was excellent as you would expect in Bali. 

I think the highlight was the food and communal area. The breakfasts were outstanding. Nothing was too much for the staff who went out of their way to make sure the kids were happy and full up! The Menu is concise, wholesome and delicious, especially the breakfast cake which is baked fresh each morning. We also loved the granola and the kids adored the freshly made pancakes and tasty Tease Toast. The Indonesian spiced chicken and beef curry was also delicious as was the satay which the chef said was a new item they were trying! I told him to keep it on the menu! 

The best bit about Origin is literally when you walk in and are confronted by a very peaceful, stylish and landscaped garden with pool and fire which lights up each evening. The lighting in the trees above the pool is also a great touch which gives this place a very relaxing ambience. Each night the staff offered the kids marshmallows to cook over the fire whilst we sipped their unique, home-made cocktails. 

You really feel like you can fully relax after a busy day and the whole hotel is an oasis. You’re literally 10 minutes from all the surf beaches and beach clubs in Uluwatu so can head out each day for surfing, lunches and shopping. They provide complimentary snorkeling equipment as well as surf boards, boogie boards, bicycles and skateboards! 

Finally an important mention to the staff who will make your stay memorable. They go above and beyond to ensure everything is perfect. Always happy to chat and genuinely interested in your day and ensuring it's a relaxing holiday. We will definitely be back!

Our villa was very comfortable and private. Complete with Aircon, tv and very speedy internet. 
Our son and daughter are surfers and enjoyed their days on the waves, while we relaxed in our villa’s pool.
Origin is located a bit away from the main Uluwatu area, yet there are great restaurants within walking distance. We stayed 4 nights and are already making plans to come back soon!

text:
We stayed for 4 nights at Origin Uluwatu. The tents are a really cool concept and totally different to anything we have seen or experienced in Bali - they have an internal structure, aircon, hot shower and outdoor bathroom, yet you are staying in a big luxury tent. The tent is surrounded by a huge walled garden so you feel like you have lots of space to relax and are also very private.
We stayed in a pool tent, which was great to cool off in the Bali heat within the privacy of your room. There is also a big pool in the main garden area with a pool-side bar and restaurant. 
Breakfast is a daily changing menu with a great selection (I recommend the overnight oats), and is served to your covered outdoor dining area in your tent.
The staff are excellent! They really make the stay memorable and nothing was too much trouble, they were always available and always discreet.
We will definitely be coming back to Origin - it would be great for a couple, a group of friends, or a family with kids.
title: A really cool luxury tent hotel!
